Ar Scath na Sleibhte

Travel Documentary hosted by Cormac hAdhmaill, published by BBC in 2015 - Irish narration. 
http://docuwiki.net/images/d/d7/Ar-Scath-na-Sleibhte-Cover.jpg

Information
------------------------------
Cormac Cormac hAdhmaill explores the mountains of Ulster with the people who live and work around them.
Part 1. Cnoic Aontroma (The Antrim Hills)
Cormac walks through the Antrim Hills in search of the story of the Feis na nGleann and pays a visit to Glenarm Castle.
Part 2. Binn Chuilceach (Cuilcagh)
From Cuilcagh Mountain, County Fermanagh, Cormac reveals how the Marble Arch caves were discovered and visits the historic Florence Court House.
Part 3. SlÃ©ibhte Chuailnge (The Cooley Mountains)
Cormac explores the historic Cooley Mountains and rich Gaelic culture of the surrounding area.
Part 4. Cnoic BhÃ©al Feirste (The Belfast Hills)
Cormac explores the secret sites of the Belfast Hills and hears the stories of the people passionate about this landscape.
